Want to keep him
here with you?

710
00:41:59,000 --> 00:42:01,000
Let's do a rhythm strip.

711
00:42:01,000 --> 00:42:02,000
We did one
two weeks ago.

712
00:42:02,000 --> 00:42:03,000
Yeah, I know.

713
00:42:03,000 --> 00:42:06,000
That little click
every ten heartbeats or so

714
00:42:06,000 --> 00:42:07,000
seems a little more
frequent now.

715
00:42:07,000 --> 00:42:09,000
It might mean nothing

716
00:42:09,000 --> 00:42:11,000
but I'm going to do a strip
and send it to Kaplan

717
00:42:11,000 --> 00:42:13,000
see if he wants
to do an echo.

718
00:42:13,000 --> 00:42:15,000
It may be nothing,
believe me.

719
00:42:15,000 --> 00:42:17,000
I... am an old woman
kind of guy.

720
00:42:17,000 --> 00:42:19,000
I check the locks
on every door.

721
00:42:19,000 --> 00:42:22,000
David, tell me the truth.

722
00:42:22,000 --> 00:42:24,000
The truth is the same
as it's always been.

723
00:42:24,000 --> 00:42:27,000
She's surprised us too often
for me and Kaplan

724
00:42:27,000 --> 00:42:29,000
to have a timetable.

725
00:42:29,000 --> 00:42:32,000
I know that's hard.

726
00:42:32,000 --> 00:42:36,000
( rhythmic beeps )

727
00:42:42,000 --> 00:42:44,000
Good.

728
00:42:44,000 --> 00:42:46,000
Maaaa.

729
00:42:47,000 --> 00:42:50,000
Here you go.

730
00:42:50,000 --> 00:42:51,000
Mmm, thanks.

731
00:42:51,000 --> 00:42:52,000
Hmm.

732
00:42:52,000 --> 00:42:54,000
( sighs contentedly )

733
00:42:54,000 --> 00:42:57,000
Amy left this on my desk
at the library.

734
00:42:57,000 --> 00:43:00,000
"I learned a word,
it's "serendipity.

735
00:43:00,000 --> 00:43:02,000
"When you say it,
it sounds skippity.

736
00:43:02,000 --> 00:43:04,000
"Light and airy,
just by chance

737
00:43:04,000 --> 00:43:08,000
a breeze that makes
the flowers dance."

738
00:43:08,000 --> 00:43:09,000
"Skippity."

739
00:43:09,000 --> 00:43:10,000
It's nice, huh?

740
00:43:10,000 --> 00:43:12,000
I like that.

741
00:43:14,000 --> 00:43:17,000
Hmm...

742
00:43:17,000 --> 00:43:20,000
Amy is what I imagine
Julia would be like.

743
00:43:20,000 --> 00:43:23,000
Smart... messy and awkward,
you know?

744
00:43:23,000 --> 00:43:26,000
Full of questions.

745
00:43:26,000 --> 00:43:29,000
( sighs )

746
00:43:31,000 --> 00:43:34,000
I had so many plans
when I got married.

747
00:43:34,000 --> 00:43:37,000
You sound like your life has
been folded up and put away.

748
00:43:37,000 --> 00:43:38,000
But it's not over.

749
00:43:41,000 --> 00:43:44,000
The carnival opened
in Blair County.

750
00:43:44,000 --> 00:43:46,000
You know, Amy's never been.

751
00:43:46,000 --> 00:43:47,000
We should take the girls.

752
00:43:47,000 --> 00:43:49,000
Oh, it's two hours away.

753
00:43:49,000 --> 00:43:50,000
Thursday's my last day
at the library.

754
00:43:50,000 --> 00:43:53,000
We could go Friday afternoon
and avoid the traffic.

755
00:43:53,000 --> 00:43:55,000
All right.

756
00:44:00,000 --> 00:44:02,000
I know you made us
promise no fuss

757
00:44:02,000 --> 00:44:03,000
but this doesn't
feel right.

758
00:44:03,000 --> 00:44:05,000
Well, you'll
get your chance

759
00:44:05,000 --> 00:44:06,000
at the Book Lovers Ball.

760
00:44:06,000 --> 00:44:08,000
You can make as many
speeches as you want.

761
00:44:08,000 --> 00:44:10,000
I'll play the fool
for a big donation.

762
00:44:10,000 --> 00:44:12,000
You'll play the guest
of honor and like it.

763
00:44:12,000 --> 00:44:14,000
Aw. Well, we'll see.

764
00:44:14,000 --> 00:44:15,000
( chuckling )

765
00:44:17,000 --> 00:44:19,000
Goodbye, Mrs. Parker.

766
00:44:19,000 --> 00:44:21,000
We'll miss you.

767
00:44:21,000 --> 00:44:23,000
Yeah.

